lab: your machine using Tor?

you are a SOC analyst

A user reports slow internet. The security team suspects Tor is running on the machine.
Your job:
1. Identify Tor processes
2. Find Tor ports
3. Discover relay connections
4. Capture evidence
5. Write an incident report

step1:Host Enumeration
  identify running process.

"ps aux | grep tor"

Expected:
-->>debian-tor 1234 ...../user/bin/tor

step2:Find Listening ports

"ss -tulnp"

look for:
-->>127.0.0.1:9050
    127.0.0.1:9051

investigation notes:
port        purpose
9050        SOCKS Proxy
9051        Control port

step3: Map Process to Network Connections

"sudo ss -tpn"  (or)   "sudo lsof -i"
Example:
-->>tor 1234 ESTAB 185.x.x.x:443

step4:Identify Tor Relays
check current public ip
"torsocks curl ifconfig.me"

now collect relay IPs:
"sudo ss -tpn | grep ESTAB"

step5:Packet Capture
open wireshark:
"sudo wireshark"

capture:
"wlan0"

generate Tor traffic:
"torsocks curl https://check.torproject.org"

step6:Traffic Hunting
"sudo tcpdump -i wlan0"

filter"
"sudo tcpdump -i wlan0 host <relay-ip>

look for: tcp syn
          tcp ack
          tls handshake


step7:Build a Timeline
"watch -n 2 'ss -tpn' "

step8: Log Analysis
"journalctl -u tor"


step9: Threat Hunting Challenge
"ss -tulnp"

Step 10: SOC Incident Report
Write:

Executive Summary

Host Investigation:
- Process identified
- PID identified
- Listening ports identified

Network Investigation:
- Relay IPs observed
- TLS traffic observed

Assessment:
Tor activity confirmed

Recommendation:
Verify if Tor usage is authorized
Monitor outbound relay connections


note: this topic only how internet suspects Tor is running on the machine